  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions or legitimate businesses. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through multiple transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the money into the economy as apparently legitimate funds\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but most involve intentionally disguising the origins of money obtained through criminal activities.",
